Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.42,0:00:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Each year, we look forward\Nto the high-quality video presentations
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.09,0:00:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that have become\Na highlight of our conventions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.05,0:00:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Work is underway\Non videos and dramas for future conventions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.51,0:00:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The set construction
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.51,0:00:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and other work needed for the series
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.52,0:00:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs16}{\fnArial}The Good News According to Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.56,0:00:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is well along.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.56,0:00:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, planning and construction\Nof our new media production facility
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.32,0:00:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States\Nis moving ahead steadily.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.95,0:00:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these efforts\Nare supported by voluntary donations.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.58,0:00:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you would like to have a share
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.62,0:00:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in supporting the worldwide work\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.71,0:01:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,one way you can do so
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.75,0:01:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is through your financial contributions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.09,0:01:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,For more information,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.09,0:01:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,please visit donate.jw.org.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.97,0:01:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We have seen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.97,0:01:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah promises us a future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.60,0:01:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,filled with happiness and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.85,0:01:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How will universal peace come about,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.19,0:01:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and what will it mean for mankind?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.07,0:01:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Please pay close attention\Nto Brother Geoffrey Jackson,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.28,0:01:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a member of the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.32,0:01:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,as he answers those questions\Nin the final talk of this convention,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.16,0:01:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,entitled “Universal Peace Is Sure to Come!”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.26,0:01:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What is true peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.22,0:01:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,For those who live in lands\Nwhere they have wars,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.14,0:02:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,no doubt the focus they have on true peace
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.48,0:02:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is to stop fighting, to stop the conflicts,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.23,0:02:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to not have any wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.02,0:02:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s true that peace\Ndoes include an absence of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.95,0:02:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But in many cases, the efforts of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.95,0:02:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and gain peace by stopping wars
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.49,0:02:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is similar to what we say\Nis a Band-Aid solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.21,0:02:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.92,0:02:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a person may have a horrible sore,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.09,0:02:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps even cancerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.13,0:02:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And if he just puts a Band-Aid over the top,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.30,0:02:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe it hides the sore,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.84,0:02:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but it really doesn’t solve the problem\N—does it?—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.35,0:02:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because peace is not just an end of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.81,0:02:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You know yourself, if you were to live\Nin a country where there isn’t any war
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but you’re still worried about your health,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.94,0:02:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,your well-being, and your safety
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:02:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,or if you feel sick and hungry,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.87,0:03:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,would you say that you’re having\Na peaceful life?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.66,0:03:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.91,0:03:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the Bible, the word “peace”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.33,0:03:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,means far more than just an absence of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.71,0:03:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It means good health, well-being, and safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.76,0:03:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And from our convention, we’ve seen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.26,0:03:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that there’s a lot involved with true peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.47,0:03:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It includes having\Na peaceful relationship with Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.93,0:03:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It also means having\Na peaceful relationship with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.56,0:03:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And also it includes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.03,0:03:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the peace of heart and mind\Nthat gives us tranquility.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.45,0:03:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But now in this final talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.99,0:03:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to consider a bigger issue,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.91,0:03:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is universal peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.54,0:03:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what do we mean by universal peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What we mean by universal peace\Nis a type of peace
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.88,0:04:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that is everywhere in heaven and on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.18,0:04:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—in all aspects of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.47,0:04:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the type of peace that only the God\Nof peace, Jehovah, can bring
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.31,0:04:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,along with the “Prince of Peace,”\NJesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.31,0:04:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon they will take dramatic steps
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.32,0:04:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,toward the restoration of universal peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.99,0:04:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s take our Bibles,\Nand if we turn together
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.95,0:04:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to Romans 16:20,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.70,0:04:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll see what’s included
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.91,0:04:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in this restoration of universal peace
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.21,0:04:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,—that’s Romans 16:20.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.63,0:04:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There we’re told: “For his part,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.38,0:04:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“the God who gives peace will crush Satan
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.14,0:04:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“under your feet shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.56,0:04:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,May the undeserved kindness\Nof our Lord Jesus be with you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.69,0:04:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the restoration of universal peace\Nalso includes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.48,0:04:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the crushing of Satan the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.53,0:05:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So in our final discussion,\Nthe final talk of this convention,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.28,0:05:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to consider four basic questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.29,0:05:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The first one is,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.29,0:05:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,When was universal peace disturbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.83,0:05:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, Who will restore universal peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.67,0:05:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The third question, How will it be restored?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.43,0:05:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And then finally, we’re going to think\Nabout what further blessings
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.68,0:05:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind will enjoy at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.18,0:05:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But before we go on\Nto answer those questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.44,0:05:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s review together\Nthe program that we’ve had.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.27,0:05:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you’ll agree that this has been\Na beautiful convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.40,0:05:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s encouraged us to pursue peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.45,0:05:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But what are some of the good points\Nthat you remember from the program?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.24,0:05:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as we mentioned already, there are\Nthree aspects to peace that we’ll discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.25,0:05:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, our peace with Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.42,0:06:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Friday program finished\Nwith the final talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.92,0:06:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s where it mentions\Nabout not being misled
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.76,0:06:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,by imitation peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.39,0:06:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Sunday,\Nwhat a beautiful public discourse we had!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.10,0:06:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It said “Friendship With God—How Possible?”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the second aspect of our peace
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.32,0:06:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is peace with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.49,0:06:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The first day, remember,\Nwe had that beautiful symposium
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,on family peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.99,0:06:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What were some of the things\Nthat we need to do
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.41,0:06:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to have peace in our family?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.62,0:06:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, love and respect are important.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.33,0:06:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to improve\Nour communication with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.21,0:06:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to work as a team\Nand worship together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.55,0:06:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Saturday, we had\Nanother interesting symposium
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.76,0:06:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,on what it said about peace wreckers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.39,0:06:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,things that can wreck peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.85,0:06:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember some of those?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.85,0:06:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Inappropriate boasting,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.27,0:07:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,envy, dishonesty, harmful gossip,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.78,0:07:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and uncontrolled anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.11,0:07:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the third aspect of peace
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.16,0:07:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,deals with our personal peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.66,0:07:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,our inner calm despite trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.04,0:07:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,On Saturday, we had a very interesting talk
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.75,0:07:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that mentioned the need\Nto safeguard our bond of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.05,0:07:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then on Sunday, we went through\Nanother symposium where it gave examples
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.05,0:07:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of those who had sowed peace\Nand then reaped peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,As we look through the program,\NI’m sure there are so many points
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.73,0:07:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can remember that you enjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.19,0:07:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, one of the highlights\Nat any convention
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.57,0:07:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is when we have the baptism.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.07,0:07:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were baptized at this convention,\Nwe’d like to welcome you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.99,0:07:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we welcome you\Nto the Christian brotherhood
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.24,0:07:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because we know that you’re working hard\Nto have peace with Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.71,0:08:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But now at this point, let’s watch a video
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.75,0:08:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that gives us some lessons\Nwith regard to what we saw
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.59,0:08:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in the various videos in this convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.55,0:08:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.27,0:08:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everyone, Brooke here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.39,0:08:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess who just walked in?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.73,0:08:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Olivia.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.90,0:08:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And there’s Jake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.02,0:08:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Would she ever?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.27,0:08:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she would never; she’s an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels out of your control, doesn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.45,0:08:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember when we studied\Nabout the Shulammite girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.16,0:08:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was really in control?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.75,0:08:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,She was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.50,0:08:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the same power.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.75,0:08:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you believe that,\Nit’ll change how you handle the pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.80,0:08:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My peace comes from doing the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.13,0:08:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“I am a wall.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.31,0:08:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re just a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.10,0:08:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.14,0:09:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about what the jailer had done to Paul.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.64,0:09:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have hated him for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.02,0:09:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he could have.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.77,0:09:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But I guess he saw the jailer’s pain\Ninstead of just his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.49,0:09:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me show you just one scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.86,0:09:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, one scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.95,0:09:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has taught us to love,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.16,0:09:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s given our family
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.04,0:09:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.34,0:09:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Haley from DeNure Design here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.26,0:09:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t think she’s showing off?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.22,0:09:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this just about Haley?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.97,0:09:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you believe her?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.31,0:09:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven’t seen all her posts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.27,0:09:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If Celia agrees that Haley\Nis doing something she shouldn’t,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.23,0:09:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you should talk to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.23,0:09:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.69,0:09:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,your posts lately on QuicPost.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.69,0:09:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.19,0:09:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people might think you’re bragging.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.11,0:09:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would think like that?\NYou?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.57,0:09:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t want to upset you.\NJake said that I needed to take . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.49,0:09:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Jake! So everyone thinks\Nmy posts are inappropriate?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.62,0:10:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not what I am saying at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You are such . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.08,0:10:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Think back to a time
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.13,0:10:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when you wanted forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.47,0:10:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“Love is patient and kind.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.09,0:10:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.85,0:10:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry, Haley.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.23,0:10:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Genuine affection fights peace wreckers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.40,0:10:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And affection grows when we really know
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.15,0:10:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.99,0:10:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I was always impressed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.99,0:10:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,with how close you two were.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.41,0:10:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it wasn’t always that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.50,0:10:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.79,0:10:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What started as a small disagreement\Njust exploded.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.13,0:10:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You!\NYou’re the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.05,0:10:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed a lot of help from Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:10:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to make things right with Nick.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.51,0:11:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a misunderstanding
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.51,0:11:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that got blown all out of proportion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.39,0:11:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn’t handle it the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.73,0:11:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s when our peace\Nwas really put to the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.32,0:11:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The body decided, unanimously,\Nthat he should no longer serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.69,0:11:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you pushed them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.91,0:11:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Phil didn’t know just how tense things were\Nbetween Tim and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.54,0:11:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I found comfort\Nin accounts of Jehovah’s servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.79,0:11:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They helped me realize that 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.38,0:11:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,being at peace with my brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.38,0:11:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,was more important\Nthan any appointed position.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.17,0:11:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t easy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.18,0:11:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but we talked it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.51,0:11:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were able to make peace\Nwith Jehovah’s help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.47,0:11:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Without peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.48,0:11:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know how we could’ve managed\Nwhat was to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.52,0:11:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment when you hear the verdict
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.73,0:11:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’ll stay in prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.78,0:11:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s like you’ve been knocked unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.66,0:12:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But then
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.33,0:12:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the doors of the elevator opened up,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.33,0:12:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and in front of us . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.51,0:12:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.55,0:12:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When you’re just about to lose\Nall your strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.22,0:12:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah does that something for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.18,0:12:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The Russian brothers and sisters,\NI pray for them constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.02,0:12:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are going\Nthrough a very tough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.66,0:12:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What I’ve learned from all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.45,0:12:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is peace isn’t from what’s outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.75,0:12:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,from what’s going on,\Nor from what you’re experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.21,0:12:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve learned that peace is on the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.25,0:13:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and that comes from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.39,0:13:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What priceless lessons those were!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.60,0:13:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, at this point, friends,\Nwe’re going to turn our attention
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.27,0:13:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to that bigger issue
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.65,0:13:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,—universal peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.78,0:13:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the first question\Nwe’re going to answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.24,0:13:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,When was universal peace disturbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.41,0:13:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Before mankind was created,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.46,0:13:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,universal peace existed for countless ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.96,0:13:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just like a beautiful pond of water
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.17,0:13:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that was undisturbed\N—no ripples, mirrorlike in appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.64,0:13:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, there was\Nutmost harmony with Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and with all the spirit creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.73,0:13:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But then it’s just as if a rock was thrown
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.61,0:13:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,into that beautiful pond
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.77,0:14:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and peace started to be disturbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.99,0:14:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When do you think that happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.45,0:14:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’ll find the answer to that question\Nby turning to the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.79,0:14:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and this time, if we look at 1 John 3:8
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.92,0:14:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,—that’s 1 John 3:8—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.88,0:14:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,notice the answer to the question,\NWhen did the problem start?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.05,0:14:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There we’re told: “The one who practices sin
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.26,0:14:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“originates with the Devil,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.81,0:14:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“because the Devil has been sinning\Nfrom the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.02,0:14:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“For this purpose the Son of God\Nwas made manifest,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.57,0:14:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to break up the works of the Devil.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.32,0:14:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So notice the answer to the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.95,0:14:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“Because the Devil has been sinning\Nfrom the beginning,”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.62,0:14:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or, as the footnote says,\N‘from the time that he began.’
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.00,0:14:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean right from the very time\Nwhen he was created?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.38,0:15:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No, he wasn’t the Devil then, was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.17,0:15:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a perfect angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.63,0:15:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So when was it
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.63,0:15:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that this universal peace\Nstarted to be disturbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.56,0:15:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When was it that the ripples\Nstarted to go through the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.56,0:15:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you might remember
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.10,0:15:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that it wasn’t at the time\Nthat he deceived Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.78,0:15:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a little bit like when the Bible says\Na woman gives birth to a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.78,0:15:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s not when the child’s life starts,\Nis it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.49,0:15:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts well before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.49,0:15:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So likewise, this disruption\Nof the universal peace
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.29,0:15:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,began in heaven first,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.83,0:15:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time that the angel who became Satan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.21,0:15:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,started to covet the position of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.22,0:15:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to want worship from others.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.97,0:15:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And by doing this,\Nhe alienated himself from God
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.26,0:15:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and no longer was he in harmony\Nwith Jehovah’s will.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.18,0:15:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Then that sinful attitude
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.10,0:16:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,was manifested in the garden of Eden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.77,0:16:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s when he took the next step
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.94,0:16:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and started to disturb the peace\Nof Adam and Eve
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.24,0:16:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and, of course,\Nthey lost their peace with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.83,0:16:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But let’s take a moment and think
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.83,0:16:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,about what was really involved
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.16,0:16:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,with those events\Nthere in the garden of Eden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.88,0:16:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Some very important issues were raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.88,0:16:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember how Satan, first of all,\Nspoke to Eve?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.64,0:16:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked what seemed\Nlike a ridiculous question: ‘Is it true
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.27,0:16:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,‘that God hasn’t allowed you to eat\Nfrom any tree in the garden?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.31,0:16:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All the trees are banned?’
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.31,0:16:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course, that’s ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.98,0:16:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But what was he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.19,0:16:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He was calling into question\NJehovah’s qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.20,0:16:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he was inferring\Nthat Jehovah may not be so generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.99,0:16:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he’s stingy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.45,0:16:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he’s holding things back\Nfrom Adam and Eve
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.75,0:17:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that they really should have.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.58,0:17:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Satan went one step further.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.59,0:17:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: “You . . . will not die.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.59,0:17:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Really what he was saying is,\N‘Jehovah is a liar.’
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.56,0:17:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What a horrible accusation!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.35,0:17:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, Eve didn’t defend Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.90,0:17:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We would have expected\Nthat she would have said to Satan:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.94,0:17:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Who are you? I don’t know you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.07,0:17:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Why would I believe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.07,0:17:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I know my loving heavenly Father, Jehovah.’
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.53,0:17:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But no, she sided with the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.92,0:17:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what would Jehovah do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.25,0:17:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, think for a moment about this:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.38,0:17:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What if someone accused you wrongly\Nin front of everybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.34,0:17:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,calling you a liar,\Nsaying all sorts of bad things about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.06,0:18:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you go and punch them in the face?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.98,0:18:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you did, that wouldn’t be\Nthe right thing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.73,0:18:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and it certainly wouldn’t answer\Nthe questions raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.19,0:18:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, was that person really true\Nin what they said or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.15,0:18:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you probably solve this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.03,0:18:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you might take the person to court.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.04,0:18:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that court case, that person
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.25,0:18:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,could offer whatever evidence they feel\Nthey have to prove that you’re a liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.63,0:18:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,\Nyou can produce witnesses to prove
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.51,0:18:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that really you aren’t a liar,\Nbut you’re very truthful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.22,0:18:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then finally, there would be\Na decision made
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.26,0:18:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as to who was right and who was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.47,0:18:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in a similar way,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.69,0:18:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,these issues (these questions)\Nraised in the garden of Eden
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.19,0:18:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,started a symbolic court case.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.57,0:18:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So how did Jehovah respond?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.28,0:18:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wisely, he allowed time
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.57,0:18:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to settle these issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.91,0:19:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He allowed Satan the opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.74,0:19:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and rule mankind to do things his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.38,0:19:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, mercifully,\Nhe provided the hope
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.88,0:19:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for the unborn children of Adam and Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.76,0:19:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember at Genesis 3:15,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.10,0:19:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it speaks of an “offspring,” or a Son,\Nwho’d come later
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.81,0:19:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually undo the bad
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.89,0:19:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that Satan had done there in the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.27,0:19:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually free mankind\Nfrom sin and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.74,0:19:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But what has Satan been doing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.86,0:19:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,since this opportunity has been given to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.99,0:19:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s still craving worship from other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.66,0:19:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants them to bow down to him\Nand acknowledge him as their god.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.46,0:19:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He also uses lies and deceit
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.33,0:19:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to ‘blind the minds’ of persons.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.50,0:19:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he also has great anger,\Nparticularly at this time in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.84,0:19:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,where he knows his end is near.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.09,0:20:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he’s influencing the world to hate
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.01,0:20:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,anyone who stands up on Jehovah’s side.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.44,0:20:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, let’s think\Nabout a very interesting question:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.44,0:20:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we’re living
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.69,0:20:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,in a world that is ruled by Satan,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.69,0:20:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is it possible at all
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.28,0:20:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for us to have a measure of peace with God?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.74,0:20:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re experiencing\Nso many trials and challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.20,0:20:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We face opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.75,0:20:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We have illness, economic problems,\Ndisasters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.88,0:20:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible to have some measure of peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.01,0:20:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is found again in the Scriptures,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.93,0:20:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and this time, if you turn with me, please,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.47,0:20:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to the book of 2 Corinthians chapter 1
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.39,0:20:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—Second Corinthians 1:3, 4—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.90,0:20:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,notice this beautiful promise:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.65,0:21:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“Praised be the God and Father\Nof our Lord Jesus Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.20,0:21:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“the Father of tender mercies
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.45,0:21:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the God of all comfort,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.33,0:21:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“who comforts us in all our trials
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.83,0:21:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that we may be able to comfort others\Nin any sort of trial
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.38,0:21:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with the comfort that we receive from God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.38,0:21:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that a beautiful scripture?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.05,0:21:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it highlight?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.85,0:21:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, Jehovah obviously is aware\Nof our suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.72,0:21:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He feels for us.\NHe wants to help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.73,0:21:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It mentions he’s\N“the Father of tender mercies.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.40,0:21:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the same time, we realize
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.03,0:21:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah won’t step in\Nand fix all our problems at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.03,0:21:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.03,0:21:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is the time that Satan
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.49,0:21:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,has the opportunity\Nto try and rule the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.83,0:21:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the problems of this world\Nreally come from Satan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.25,0:21:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time,\Nwe wouldn’t expect Jehovah to step in
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.84,0:22:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and start to solve the problems\Nas if he were helping Satan the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.55,0:22:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is a time\Nwhen Satan will be taken away
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.14,0:22:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the problems will be solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.35,0:22:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We could think of Jehovah’s position\Nas similar to that of a father
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.40,0:22:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,whose son is running in a marathon race.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.48,0:22:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As he sees his son running in the race,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.91,0:22:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he may see his son is starting to tire out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.07,0:22:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, perhaps you may see that others\Nin the race are not obeying the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.25,0:22:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean that the father then jumps in\Nand takes the place of his son
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.54,0:22:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and helps him as he runs along?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.25,0:22:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the rules don’t allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.80,0:22:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But what the father can do\Nis continue to encourage his son:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.38,0:22:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“Keep on going.\NYes, you can do it!”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.05,0:22:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a similar way,\Nwhat does this verse tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.35,0:22:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It said that Jehovah gives us comfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.69,0:22:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How does he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.69,0:23:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He gives us peace\Nby means of his Word, the Bible;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.19,0:23:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,by means of holy spirit;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.28,0:23:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and by the loving brotherhood that we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.87,0:23:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So at this point, what we’d like to do\Nis have a look at a video that will highlight
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.87,0:23:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,how Jehovah lovingly helps us\Neven in times of need.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.51,0:23:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We are living
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.68,0:23:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in “critical times
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.55,0:23:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,hard to deal with.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.60,0:23:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Many people have lost all hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.56,0:23:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and servants of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.94,0:23:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,are not free from trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.40,0:23:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We may face loss of property,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.86,0:23:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of health,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.62,0:23:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of loved ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.04,0:23:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We may experience deep emotional trauma
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.29,0:24:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,or even imprisonment for our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.80,0:24:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Our trials are similar to those of Job,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.31,0:24:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a faithful servant of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.98,0:24:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who was so saddened that he once asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.56,0:24:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Why didn’t I die at birth?’
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.48,0:24:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we’ve had moments like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.28,0:24:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But why should we not lose hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.29,0:24:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because with every trial\Ncomes Jehovah’s support
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.87,0:24:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—support received in many forms:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.38,0:24:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,material support,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.06,0:25:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,emotional support,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.66,0:25:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and spiritual support.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.39,0:25:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And while Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.39,0:25:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,will not remove all our trials now,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.81,0:25:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we trust that with his support,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.52,0:25:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we can endure them
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.40,0:25:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,until they disappear\Nin “the real life” to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.82,0:25:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 34:17, 18 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.82,0:25:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“They cried out, and Jehovah heard . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.49,0:26:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He saves those who are crushed in spirit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.25,0:26:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can see that even though\Nour peace has been disturbed,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.92,0:26:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we can enjoy peace with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.59,0:26:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s think about our second question.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.89,0:26:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, that question was,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.93,0:26:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Who will restore universal peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.94,0:26:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we already saw the answer
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.94,0:26:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when we referred to Genesis 3:15,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.52,0:26:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the first prophecy in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.69,0:26:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It mentioned the promised offspring, or Son,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.95,0:26:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and that one is Jesus Christ\N—the Prince of Peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.87,0:26:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He has the key role
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.99,0:26:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in restoring universal peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.41,0:26:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Very soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.42,0:26:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s going to take the decisive action\Nto remove this old world
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.80,0:26:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and then take progressive steps
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.59,0:26:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,toward the restoration of universal peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.47,0:27:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But why can we be so sure
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.26,0:27:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jesus will come soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.10,0:27:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a very simple answer
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.19,0:27:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—by seeing the current events\Nthat are happening in the world today.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.07,0:27:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, as we look around us,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.23,0:27:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we see so many things that are happening
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.15,0:27:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that proves to us
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.36,0:27:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jesus will soon step in to help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.62,0:27:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how can we say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.62,0:27:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s have a look together
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.79,0:27:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,at the famous prophecy\Nthat’s recorded in Matthew chapter 24
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.00,0:27:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,—Matthew 24:3.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.68,0:27:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, the apostles\Nat this particular time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.60,0:27:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,were asking Jesus a very important question.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.39,0:27:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s at the second part of verse 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.60,0:27:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It says they asked: “Tell us,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.77,0:27:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“when will these things be,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.44,0:27:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“and what will be the sign of your presence
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.28,0:28:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and of the conclusion\Nof the system of things?”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.37,0:28:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you remember, no doubt\Nfrom your previous studies of the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.00,0:28:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,how Jesus then went on to list\Nmany events that would occur
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.96,0:28:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,during the last days.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.17,0:28:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He mentioned wars;
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.17,0:28:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,he mentioned earthquakes;\Nhe mentioned famines
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.76,0:28:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and all sorts of pestilences.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.43,0:28:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly we have seen those things happen\Nin recent times.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.23,0:28:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to all of that, Matthew 24:14
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.65,0:28:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned the need to preach\Nthe “good news of the Kingdom.”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.40,0:28:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But there could be some who\Nperhaps may doubt a little
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.20,0:28:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and say: ‘Well, there’s been wars\Nall through time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.16,0:28:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,‘There’s been earthquakes at other times,\Nnot just in the last days,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.75,0:28:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and food shortages.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.79,0:28:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,‘So why can we be so sure
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.79,0:28:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,‘that this is the time
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.09,0:28:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,‘when we know that Jesus\Nwill soon bring about
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.76,0:29:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,an end to wickedness?’
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.39,0:29:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s use an illustration.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.14,0:29:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of us are familiar\Nwith using a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.85,0:29:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when you sit at your computer,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.94,0:29:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what’s the first thing that you need to do\Nafter you’ve turned it on?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.52,0:29:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, you have to type in a password,\Ndon’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.61,0:29:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to get it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.32,0:29:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to put in all those numbers\Nand letters that are required.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.70,0:29:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you won’t be able\Nto start working on the computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.66,0:29:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these days people are very concerned
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.25,0:29:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,about having strong passwords.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.30,0:29:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think if you had a password
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.47,0:29:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that had 24 different letters and numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.76,0:29:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a very strong password,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.31,0:29:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and it would be very difficult for someone
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.06,0:29:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to just randomly try and find out\Nwhat those numbers are
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.10,0:29:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and unlock your computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.94,0:30:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how does that relate\Nto the sign that Jesus gave?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.69,0:30:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice that if you look back at Matthew 24:3,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.28,0:30:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the question was not\Nthe “signs” of your presence
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.70,0:30:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but the “sign.”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.83,0:30:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like a password—one sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.58,0:30:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But then that sign\Nhas many different features
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.05,0:30:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,—in fact, at least 24 different features.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.93,0:30:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So even though there have been wars\Nin the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.35,0:30:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the time when we see
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.35,0:30:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,all those features\Ncoming together at one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.10,0:30:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that way, we could say\Nit opens the fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.73,0:30:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of Bible prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.07,0:30:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, as we look around us,\Nas we listen to the news each day,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.45,0:30:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we can see\Nthat there is a definite fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.08,0:30:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of what Jesus said.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.08,0:30:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, the end is close.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.16,0:30:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just like a jigsaw puzzle,\Nto use another illustration.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.04,0:30:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,When you have all the pieces\Nof a jigsaw puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.75,0:31:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and you start to put them all together,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.88,0:31:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually when all the pieces are in place,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.13,0:31:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the picture is clear, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.30,0:31:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s exactly how we should feel
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.06,0:31:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,about the prophecy that Jesus gave.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.10,0:31:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, very soon,\Nhe is going to step in and take action.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.36,0:31:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But, of course, sometimes we may feel,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.24,0:31:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Yes, we’ve known about this\Nfor quite some time.’
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.95,0:31:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And it means that we’ve had to wait\Na long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.95,0:31:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But that doesn’t negate the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.41,0:31:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that the evidence of the last days is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.08,0:31:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we could illustrate it this way:
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.96,0:31:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of us have gone to an airport
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.38,0:31:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to meet someone\Nwho’s coming maybe from overseas
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.34,0:31:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,or another part of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.76,0:31:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, since 9/11,\Nit’s very hard to go to an airport
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.85,0:31:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and actually stand on the side of the runway\Nand see the plane land.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.85,0:31:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, what happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.86,0:32:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you get to the airport, you’re allowed\Nto go into a large room with other people,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.49,0:32:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and all you see are monitors on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.86,0:32:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what may the monitors say?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.12,0:32:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, it says there\Nthat the flight has left.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.25,0:32:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then later, maybe the monitor says\Nthe flight is on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.13,0:32:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it says the flight has landed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.92,0:32:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it says the flight is taxiing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.51,0:32:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it says it’s at the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.51,0:32:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now you start to get really excited,\Ndon’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.22,0:32:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet you haven’t seen the plane,\Nand you haven’t seen your friend yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.81,0:32:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can see from the indications
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.77,0:32:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of what you see on the monitor
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.86,0:32:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that it must be close.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.94,0:32:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And then all of a sudden, the doors open\Nand people start to come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.82,0:32:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now you’re really excited\Nbecause you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.32,0:32:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, you’re going to meet your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.16,0:32:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that is similar\Nto how we can view the last days.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.00,0:33:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There has been a lot of things happening\Nthat we don’t actually see.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.29,0:33:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But we see the indications\Nof what’s happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.84,0:33:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know that very soon
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.42,0:33:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus, the angels, and the 144,000
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.89,0:33:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,will take steps to remove this old world
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.06,0:33:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and then take further steps
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.35,0:33:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,toward the restoration of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.35,0:33:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that a beautiful promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.07,0:33:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So naturally, that takes us\Nto the third question:
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.74,0:33:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How will universal peace be restored?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.82,0:33:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What will Jesus need to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.16,0:33:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, we could say\Nthere are two actions required.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.87,0:33:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,One is to remove Satan
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.08,0:33:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and the peace disturbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.71,0:33:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the second action
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.21,0:33:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is to undo all the evil that Satan has done.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.76,0:33:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we don’t want a Band-Aid solution\N—do we?—
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.39,0:34:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,where you’re just hiding something\Nthat’s very serious
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.02,0:34:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,by putting a Band-Aid over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.40,0:34:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So not only does Jesus need to take away
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.15,0:34:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,those that are disrupting the peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.82,0:34:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but he also has to take steps
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.95,0:34:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to heal mankind and to heal the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.53,0:34:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,so that all the evil, the bad things\Nthat Satan has done,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.41,0:34:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,will be overturned.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.62,0:34:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s think about those two actions\Nfor a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.17,0:34:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, the first one\Nis to remove the peace disturbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.17,0:34:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What steps are involved with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.13,0:34:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, this is a progressive action.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.30,0:34:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If we take our Bibles\Nand turn to the book of Revelation,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.43,0:34:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll see there are several things\Nmentioned here that help us to see
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.02,0:34:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,how progressively Jesus\Nhas and will bring about
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.78,0:34:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,this removal of peace disturbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.53,0:34:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you turn with me, please,\Nto Revelation chapter 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.33,0:35:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s read together verse 9
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.87,0:35:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,—Revelation 12.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.87,0:35:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, immediately, no doubt you remember
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.54,0:35:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that Revelation 12\Nis talking about the time
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.80,0:35:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jesus’ government, his Kingdom,\Nwas established in the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.17,0:35:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That was in 1914.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.30,0:35:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 9, it mentions
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.35,0:35:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,what happened shortly after that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.10,0:35:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read it:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.10,0:35:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“So down the great dragon was hurled,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.31,0:35:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“the original serpent,\Nthe one called Devil and Satan,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.44,0:35:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“who is misleading\Nthe entire inhabited earth;
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.11,0:35:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“he was hurled down to the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.41,0:35:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and his angels were hurled down with him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.58,0:35:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice that word\Nthat came up several times
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.75,0:35:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—“hurled” down?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.75,0:35:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Jesus didn’t go and say to Satan:\N‘Well, look, if you don’t mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.59,0:35:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‘we’d like you to relocate to the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.80,0:35:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever you’re ready.’
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.88,0:36:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Satan was hurled down.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.64,0:36:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And what confidence that gives us!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.85,0:36:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that Jesus has the power
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.60,0:36:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to remove Satan from the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.73,0:36:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That gives us some idea\Nof what’s going to happen in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.77,0:36:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with regard to the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.11,0:36:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, now we’re living in a time\Nwhen Satan and his demons
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.65,0:36:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,are here in the vicinity of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.12,0:36:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and they are causing so much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.66,0:36:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what’s another step that Jesus will take
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.91,0:36:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in removing those who disrupt the peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.75,0:36:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s look at another chapter\Nin the same book,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.05,0:36:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation chapter 19
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.01,0:36:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,—Revelation chapter 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.68,0:36:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re going to read starting at verse 19\Nright through to 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.60,0:36:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We might mention before we start reading it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.44,0:36:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that here it describes\Npolitical organizations, kings,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.44,0:36:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and those who oppose\NJesus and Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.95,0:37:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And in a symbolic way,\Nit refers to these as beasts,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.70,0:37:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,as organizations,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.95,0:37:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that have disrupted the peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.50,0:37:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see what happens to them:
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.92,0:37:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“And I saw the wild beast\Nand the kings of the earth and their armies
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.21,0:37:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“gathered together to wage war\Nagainst the one seated on the horse
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.22,0:37:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“and against his army\N[now, that one is Jesus Christ].
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.22,0:37:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the wild beast was caught,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.72,0:37:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“and along with it the false prophet
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.14,0:37:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“that performed in front of it the signs
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.98,0:37:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“with which he misled those who received\Nthe mark of the wild beast
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.57,0:37:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“and those who worship its image.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.24,0:37:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“While still alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.32,0:37:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“they both were hurled into the fiery lake
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.62,0:37:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that burns with sulfur.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.95,0:37:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what happens\Nto these political organizations
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.21,0:37:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in opposition to Jehovah and Jesus?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.21,0:37:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, we see the word\N“hurled” down into destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.88,0:38:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about the rest of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.42,0:38:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that opposes Jesus’ rule?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.01,0:38:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s look at verse 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.85,0:38:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.51,0:38:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the rest were killed off
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.39,0:38:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“with the long sword\Nthat proceeded out of the mouth
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.39,0:38:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“of the one seated on the horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.90,0:38:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the birds\Nwere filled with their flesh.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.28,0:38:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that’s a very interesting comment,\Nisn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.03,0:38:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It helps us to see here
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.12,0:38:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that all those who oppose Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.66,0:38:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,will be destroyed\Nin the battle of Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.62,0:38:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s another step
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.63,0:38:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in getting ready for universal peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.26,0:38:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, Satan is cast out of heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.68,0:38:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then secondly, at Armageddon,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.14,0:38:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,all those humans who rebelled against Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.89,0:38:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and reject his rule
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.18,0:38:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,will be taken away, destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.44,0:38:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But there’s something else too.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.90,0:39:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at chapter 20 of Revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.32,0:39:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,—chapter 20 and verses 1-3:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.78,0:39:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“And I saw an angel coming down\Nout of heaven with the key of the abyss
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.62,0:39:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“and a great chain in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.83,0:39:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“He seized the dragon, the original serpent,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.17,0:39:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“who is the Devil and Satan,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.17,0:39:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“and bound him for 1,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.17,0:39:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“And he [notice the word again]\Nhurled him into the abyss
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.22,0:39:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“and shut it and sealed it over him,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.93,0:39:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that he would not mislead\Nthe nations anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.68,0:39:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“until the 1,000 years were ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.56,0:39:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,After this he must be released\Nfor a little while.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.11,0:39:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we notice from this description?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.03,0:39:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, gradually, in a progressive manner,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.61,0:39:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus will eradicate and remove
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.03,0:39:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,those who disrupt peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.87,0:39:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So Satan and his demons\Nare cast down to the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.50,0:40:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At the battle of Armageddon,\Nthose who rebelled will be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.34,0:40:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Satan will be put
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.84,0:40:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in a symbolic prison, in this abyss,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.89,0:40:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for 1,000 years along with his demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.56,0:40:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s the first action\Nthat Jesus needs to do
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.77,0:40:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,—to get rid of these troublemakers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.98,0:40:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That opens up the way\Nfor what the Bible refers to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.61,0:40:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,as the Thousand Year Reign of Jesus Christ
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.70,0:40:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,with his Kingdom and corulers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.62,0:40:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What is going to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.79,0:40:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,during that Thousand Year Reign?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.00,0:40:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember we said that it’s not\Na Band-Aid-type solution, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.96,0:40:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He will need to help
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.05,0:40:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind and the earth to heal.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.88,0:40:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, please, how this is described for us
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.09,0:40:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in a scripture that we’ve already read.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.85,0:40:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn to it again—1 John 3:8.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.94,0:41:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember in the beginning of that verse,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.48,0:41:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s where it told us how universal peace
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.57,0:41:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,was disrupted in the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.74,0:41:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time when that angel
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.95,0:41:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,became the Devil and started sinning.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.62,0:41:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But notice what it says\Nin the second part of this verse:
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.91,0:41:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“For this purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.12,0:41:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“the Son of God was made manifest,\N[to do what?]
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.25,0:41:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to break up [or to destroy]\Nthe works of the Devil.”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.80,0:41:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that an amazing concept?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.35,0:41:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus not only removes\Nthose who disrupt peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.27,0:41:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but he will “break up\Nthe works of the Devil,”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.56,0:41:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the things that he’s done\Nover these thousands of years
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.02,0:41:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that he’s been ruling this earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.28,0:41:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That means all the evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.32,0:41:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,all the suffering, death,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.57,0:41:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,all of that will be taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.87,0:41:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind will be gradually healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.16,0:42:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Jesus started to break up\Nthe works of the Devil
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.79,0:42:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,when he willingly gave his life as a ransom.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.21,0:42:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So even now we have the opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.51,0:42:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to gain a measure of peace\Nwith Jehovah and with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.30,0:42:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can ask Jehovah for forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.76,0:42:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the ransom sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.93,0:42:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But during the Thousand Year Reign,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.02,0:42:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there will be further things\Nthat Jesus will accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.36,0:42:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice these three aspects:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.94,0:42:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He will undo all harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.07,0:42:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that includes sickness, war,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.78,0:42:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,disease, famine, all these problems;
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.58,0:42:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all the harm will be undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.96,0:42:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He will also undo death
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.46,0:42:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,by resurrecting those who have died.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.84,0:42:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And he will also undo sin
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.09,0:42:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,by helping mankind to grow to perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.97,0:43:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that a beautiful promise,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.22,0:43:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,undoing all these works of the Devil?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.94,0:43:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then by the end of the thousand years,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.86,0:43:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what will we see with regard to the earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.32,0:43:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be a paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.99,0:43:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.16,0:43:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jehovah purposed it to be\Nin the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.37,0:43:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jesus, by means of the Kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.00,0:43:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will have completely broken up\Nthe works of the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.17,0:43:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, is that the time then
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.30,0:43:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when universal peace is restored?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.67,0:43:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not quite yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.89,0:43:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.97,0:43:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Something else has to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.14,0:43:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re going to reread another scripture,\Nand that’s Romans 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.27,0:43:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember we referred to that\Nin the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.52,0:43:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we see a very interesting connection
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.19,0:43:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,between two different things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.65,0:43:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s Romans 16:20:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.82,0:44:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“For his part, the God who gives peace
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.62,0:44:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“[will do what?]
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.62,0:44:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,will crush Satan under your feet shortly.”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.13,0:44:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we see the connection here?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.96,0:44:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Universal peace is connected
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.46,0:44:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with the crushing of Satan the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.76,0:44:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So universal peace can only be restored
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.01,0:44:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,after Satan has been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.85,0:44:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what events will occur\Nleading up to Satan’s destruction?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.61,0:44:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, remember,\Nas we read already in Revelation,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.69,0:44:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan is going to be allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.69,0:44:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to be released from that prison\N(the symbolic prison),
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.61,0:44:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’ll have an opportunity\Nto try to mislead
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.87,0:44:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,people who are living on the earth\Nat that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.37,0:44:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who join Satan\Nwill be destroyed forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.08,0:44:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then Satan will be permanently destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.09,0:44:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But what will happen to those perfect persons
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.30,0:45:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,who prove faithful to Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.05,0:45:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see what the Bible says
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.06,0:45:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,if we turn to the book of Romans,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.73,0:45:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Romans 8:21
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.23,0:45:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—Romans 8:21:
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.94,0:45:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“That the creation itself
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.40,0:45:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“will also be set free\Nfrom enslavement to corruption
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.41,0:45:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“and have the glorious freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.16,0:45:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of the children of God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.54,0:45:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that really mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.87,0:45:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that at that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.25,0:45:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone will become part\Nof Jehovah’s universal family.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.92,0:45:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All intelligent creatures\Nin heaven and on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.43,0:45:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,will be united as one family
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.39,0:45:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in the pure worship\Nof the one true God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.56,0:45:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful time that will be!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.35,0:45:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But what further blessings\Nare involved with this process
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.15,0:46:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of gradually bringing universal peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.15,0:46:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, during the Thousand Year Reign\Nof Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.78,0:46:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s going to be wonderful blessings.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.20,0:46:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who are obedient\Nto Jehovah and Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.87,0:46:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,will experience the things\Nthat were described
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.33,0:46:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Bible book of Psalms, in Psalm 72.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.21,0:46:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn there together
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.21,0:46:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,—Psalm 72.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.26,0:46:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we see portrayed
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.39,0:46:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,some very interesting prophetic statements
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.02,0:46:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,about the Thousand Year Reign.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.14,0:46:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll notice at the beginning,\Nit says regarding Solomon—
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.40,0:46:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So although initially\Nthis was referring to an extent
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.27,0:46:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with regard to Solomon,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.32,0:46:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus mentioned\Nthat he’s greater than Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.61,0:46:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So this has a prophetic application
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.62,0:46:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Thousand Year Reign.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.91,0:46:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see what it says about peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.66,0:46:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting in verse 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.00,0:46:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll go through to verse 4:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.50,0:47:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“O God, give your judgments to the king,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.42,0:47:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“and endow the son of the king\Nwith your righteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.55,0:47:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“May he plead the cause of your people\Nwith righteousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.55,0:47:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“and of your lowly ones with justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.97,0:47:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“May the mountains bring peace to the people,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.19,0:47:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“and may the hills bring righteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.65,0:47:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let him defend the lowly among the people,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.36,0:47:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“let him save the sons of the poor,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.90,0:47:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and let him crush the defrauder.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.57,0:47:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful description
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.83,0:47:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of what will happen\Nin the Thousand Year Reign!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.04,0:47:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, all those under Satan’s rule
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.75,0:47:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,who were lowly, beaten up, disadvantaged
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.71,0:47:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,—all these will experience relief
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.97,0:47:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the righteous rule\Nof Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.97,0:47:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go down a little further\Nto verses 12 through 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.43,0:47:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It tells us a little more\Nabout what Jesus will accomplish.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.73,0:47:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting in verse 12, we’re told:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.69,0:48:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“For he will rescue the poor\Nwho cry for help,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.15,0:48:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“also the lowly one\Nand whoever has no helper.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.57,0:48:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“He will have pity on the lowly and the poor,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.45,0:48:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the lives of the poor he will save.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.00,0:48:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“From oppression and from violence\Nhe will rescue them,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.08,0:48:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“[and notice\Nthis very interesting expression]
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.71,0:48:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and their blood will be\Nprecious in his eyes.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.55,0:48:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.05,0:48:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“Their blood will be precious in his eyes.”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.06,0:48:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Bible, usually the word “blood”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.39,0:48:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is associated with life, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.14,0:48:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s saying that each person’s life
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.69,0:48:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,will be precious to Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.61,0:48:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful description
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.24,0:48:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of what will happen\Nduring the Thousand Year Reign!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.12,0:48:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then if we go back a little to verse 5,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.91,0:49:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll notice that this part of the psalm\Nhelps us to see
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.12,0:49:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,how widespread peace will be at that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.42,0:49:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It uses very picturesque language.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.67,0:49:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice there in verse 5, it says:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.30,0:49:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“They will fear you\Nas long as there is a sun
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.64,0:49:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“[well, we know the sun continues on,\Nso they’ll continue to fear him]
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.68,0:49:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“and as long as the moon remains,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.06,0:49:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“for generation after generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.48,0:49:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“He will be like the rain\Nthat falls on the mown grass,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.07,0:49:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“like showers of rain that water the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.70,0:49:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“In his days the righteous will flourish,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.28,0:49:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“and peace will abound\Nuntil the moon is no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.25,0:49:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“He will have subjects from sea to sea
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.42,0:49:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and from the River to the ends of the earth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.59,0:49:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, what a beautiful description
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.26,0:49:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of the peaceful arrangements\Nthat will prevail
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.97,0:49:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,during the Thousand Year Reign\Nof Jesus’ Kingdom!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.43,0:50:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But then the thousand years finishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.48,0:50:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we expect when that reign ends?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.69,0:50:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure you’re going to enjoy\Nour consideration
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.78,0:50:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of a very special part of the Scriptures\N—1 Corinthians chapter 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.41,0:50:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn there with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.41,0:50:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re going to go through\Nand look at what these verses tell us
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.25,0:50:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,about after the end\Nof the Thousand Year Reign.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.21,0:50:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The section of Scripture\Nwe’re going to consider
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.88,0:50:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is 1 Corinthians chapter 15,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.80,0:50:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,verses 24-28.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.31,0:50:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting in verse 24, we’re told:
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.10,0:50:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Next, the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.56,0:50:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“when he hands over the Kingdom\Nto his God and Father,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.31,0:50:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“when he has brought to nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.40,0:50:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“all government and all authority and power.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.07,0:50:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“For he must rule as king
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.07,0:50:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“until God has put\Nall enemies under his feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.83,0:51:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the last enemy, death,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.49,0:51:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“is to be brought to nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.87,0:51:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“For God ‘subjected all things\Nunder his feet.’
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.83,0:51:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“But when he says\Nthat ‘all things have been subjected,’
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.63,0:51:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“it is evident that this does not include
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.55,0:51:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“the One who subjected all things to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.97,0:51:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“But when all things\Nwill have been subjected to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.51,0:51:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“then the Son himself\Nwill also subject himself
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.35,0:51:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“to the One who subjected all things to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.90,0:51:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that God may be all things to everyone.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.86,0:51:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What do these verses tell us\Nabout the end of the Thousand Year Reign?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.78,0:51:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s go back to verse 24.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.58,0:51:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There it says: “Next, the end . . .”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.75,0:51:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this “end” mentioned here\Nis not Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.80,0:51:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the end of the Thousand Year Reign.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.72,0:51:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the Thousand Year Reign,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.51,0:52:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,there are some other things too\Nthat will have finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.22,0:52:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That means for a start,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.23,0:52:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the end of the Kingdom arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.69,0:52:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There will also be an end to sin,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.56,0:52:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,which means that mankind will no longer need
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.94,0:52:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the ransom or a mediator or priesthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.28,0:52:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And then in verse 26, notice it says:
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.70,0:52:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“The last enemy, death,\Nis to be brought to nothing.”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.16,0:52:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the graves will be empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.96,0:52:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who have experienced the Adamic death
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.13,0:52:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,will have been brought back.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.75,0:52:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind will all attain to perfection\Nwith the end of sin
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.76,0:52:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,—Adamic sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.34,0:52:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So at that point in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.05,0:52:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,something very, very special happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.06,0:52:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.31,0:52:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s go back\Nto the beginning of our discussion
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.19,0:52:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,when we talked about the problems\Nthat occurred in the garden of Eden.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.20,0:53:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, Satan the Devil raised some issues
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.28,0:53:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that resulted in a symbolic court case
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.66,0:53:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that involves the sanctification\Nof Jehovah’s name.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.42,0:53:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Satan had claimed\Nthat Jehovah is a liar,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.59,0:53:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that he doesn’t rule mankind out of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.30,0:53:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and he even raised the question later
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.30,0:53:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,about who would actually serve Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.55,0:53:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So this issue has continued on
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.26,0:53:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,—the issue of the sanctification\Nof Jehovah’s name—right down through history.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.64,0:53:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And over and over again,\NJehovah’s name has been sanctified.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.81,0:53:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,His reputation has been vindicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.78,0:53:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see that he’s a loving God,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.78,0:53:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,unlike Satan\N—such a horrible person.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.07,0:53:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah has stood out\Nas being a loving heavenly Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.33,0:53:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So now at this point in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.79,0:53:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we can say the universal court case\Ncomes to a conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.88,0:54:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The issue is settled—the verdict is given.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.13,0:54:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In what way?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.35,0:54:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jesus has just finished ruling mankind\Nfor a thousand years,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.39,0:54:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,along with the 144,000\Nthat have made the earth a paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.31,0:54:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind is now no longer sinners;\Nthey’re perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.27,0:54:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All the problems have been healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.82,0:54:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So at this point in time, what does Jesus do?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.82,0:54:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he follow the example of Satan\Nand say: ‘Well, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.20,0:54:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I think we did a very, very good job\Nfor this thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.96,0:54:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‘So let’s just keep everything in place,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.71,0:54:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll keep on ruling in the Kingdom.’
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.88,0:54:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we saw what he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.84,0:54:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.09,0:54:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s a marvelous answer in this court case
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.89,0:54:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because Jesus hands over\Nthe Kingdom back to his Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.81,0:54:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He submits to Jehovah’s rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.98,0:54:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s just as if Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.98,0:54:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is told by his loving Son, Jesus:
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.11,0:55:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“You were right all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.53,0:55:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“This whole thing
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.53,0:55:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“has been a terrible travesty of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.07,0:55:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan is a despicable liar.”
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.99,0:55:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And all mankind, including Jesus
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.16,0:55:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and the 144,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.37,0:55:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,submit themselves to Jehovah’s rulership.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.71,0:55:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the end of the universal issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.09,0:55:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will then rule directly\Nover perfect mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.80,0:55:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But is that the point in time\Nwhen universal peace is restored?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.31,0:55:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, remember, there are some other things\Nthat need to occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.44,0:55:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve already mentioned\Nthat Satan will be released
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.44,0:55:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,from his symbolic prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.78,0:55:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll have an opportunity\Nto try and mislead some.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.36,0:55:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And for those who side with him,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.49,0:55:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah morally and ethically\Ndoesn’t have to wait any longer
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.54,0:55:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and say: ‘Well, let’s have\Nanother court case.’
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.79,0:55:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they are executed immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.38,0:56:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about the rest of mankind?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.09,0:56:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They become Jehovah’s sons and daughters.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.01,0:56:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They can talk to him directly\Nwithout the need of a mediator.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.47,0:56:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And then names will be written permanently\Nin “the book of life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.72,0:56:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll be approved\Nto live forever in Paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.06,0:56:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So at this point, when we’re thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.23,0:56:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,about all these beautiful things\Nthat will occur,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.23,0:56:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s enjoy the final video\Nof our convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.69,0:56:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It highlights the blessings\Nof the Thousand Year Reign and beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.28,0:56:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, we’re going to listen
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.99,0:56:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to the original song that we will sing\Nat the conclusion of our program.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.80,0:56:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Like an island of calm\NIn dark stormy seas,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.77,0:57:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,God’s people\Nare living in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.77,0:57:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,With our eyes of faith,\NWe see beyond the clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.53,0:57:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And know that the storm\Nsoon will cease.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.54,0:57:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,To the ends of the earth,\NThere’ll be peace at last
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.29,0:57:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,For all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.26,0:57:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,From the valleys below\NTo the mountaintops,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.47,0:57:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All creation will see\NPeace at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.65,0:57:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When the new world is here,\NAll will be one
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.74,0:58:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,On earth\Nand in heaven above.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.71,0:58:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And the peace we’ll know\NWe’ve never known before—
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.67,0:58:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A world ruled\Nby justice and love.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.68,0:58:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To the ends of the earth,\NThere’ll be peace at last
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.44,0:58:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.32,0:58:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,From the valleys below\NTo the mountaintops,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.78,0:58:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All creation will see\NPeace at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.43,0:59:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To the ends of the earth,\NThere’ll be peace at last
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.44,0:59:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.36,0:59:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,From the valleys below\NTo the mountaintops,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.41,0:59:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All creation will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.92,0:59:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To the ends of the earth,\NThere’ll be peace at last
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.88,0:59:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.80,0:59:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,From the valleys below\NTo the mountaintops,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.10,0:59:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All creation will see\NPeace at last,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.24,1:00:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace at last!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.75,1:00:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful song!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.88,1:00:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And what beautiful images to encourage us!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.47,1:00:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So brothers and sisters, we’ve enjoyed\Nour convention program, haven’t we?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.35,1:00:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us be determined to keep pursuing peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.19,1:00:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,not an imitation peace, but the real peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.06,1:00:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We can enjoy rich blessings now
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.61,1:00:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,by having a peaceful relationship\Nwith Jehovah God,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.15,1:00:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, trying to continue\Nto maintain peace with one another
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.28,1:00:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and also attaining to this inner peace\N—calmness and tranquility—
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.12,1:00:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because we have friendship\Nwith the God who gives us hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.75,1:00:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And that hope helps us to look to the future,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.05,1:00:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,even though we have difficulties now,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.34,1:00:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and we look forward to the time
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.34,1:01:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,when universal peace is finally restored.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.47,1:01:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the meantime, may the God of peace
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.97,1:01:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,be with each one of you now and forever!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.48,1:01:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Jackson.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.65,1:01:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Your talk and this entire convention\Nhave strengthened our confidence
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.65,1:01:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah’s prophetic Word
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.74,1:01:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and helped us to understand\Nhow close we are to its fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.75,1:01:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,On behalf of the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.16,1:01:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the hardworking members\Nof our Bethel families
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.79,1:01:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and translation offices around the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.71,1:01:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we thank you for watching\Nthe 2022 convention program.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.39,1:01:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We have deep appreciation and affection
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.81,1:01:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,for each one of you,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.85,1:01:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is our prayer
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.06,1:01:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah continue\Nto bless you with peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.36,1:01:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s conclude by singing a song
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.98,1:02:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that reflects the complete peace\Nthat Jehovah will soon bring about.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.57,1:02:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Please join in singing\Nthe original song
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.91,1:02:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Peace at Last!”
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.04,1:02:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which we heard during the concluding talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.75,1:02:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,After the song,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.75,1:02:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you may have your concluding prayer\Nat your individual locations.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.67,1:02:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we invite all to sing out along\Nwith the Watchtower chorus
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.47,1:02:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“Peace at Last!”
